5651.content:
At the New Year's party, a total of $$100$$ people participated in three types of performances: dancing, singing, and playing music. It is known that:  
①$$50$$ people participated in dancing, and $$40$$ people participated in playing music;  
②The number of people who only participated in singing is twice the number of people who participated in dancing;  
③$$15$$ people participated in both dancing and singing but did not participate in playing music;  
④The number of people who only participated in playing music is $$6$$ more than the number of people who participated in both playing music and singing but did not participate in dancing.  
What is the number of people who participated in both playing music and singing but did not participate in dancing?

